' FRONTEND JAVASCRIPT CLASSES
' ==========================================

package "Frontend (JavaScript)" {
  
  class RouteFinderApp <<singleton>> {
    - map : L.Map
    - currentMode : string = 'car'
    - routeLayer : L.Polyline
    - animatedMarker : L.Marker
    - animationFrameId : number
    - recognition : SpeechRecognition
    - speechSynthesis : SpeechSynthesis
    - routeData : Object
    --
    + initMap() : void
    + findRoute() : void
    + displayRoute(data, sourceLat, sourceLng, destLat, destLng) : void
    + startAnimation(path) : void
    + animateMarker(currentTime) : void
    + clearMap() : void
    + setMode(mode) : void
  }
  
  class VoiceController {
    - recognition : SpeechRecognition
    - currentVoiceTarget : string
    --
    + initVoiceRecognition() : void
    + startVoiceInput(target) : void
    + stopVoiceInput() : void
    + cleanCityName(text) : string
    + speak(text, rate) : void
    + speakRouteInfo() : void
  }
  
  class CityDatabase {
    - {static} CITY_COORDS : Map<string, [number, number]>
    --
    + {static} getCityCoords(cityName) : [number, number]
    + {static} populateCityList() : void
  }
  
  class AnimationController {
    - currentIndex : number
    - lastTime : number
    - speed : number
    --
    + startAnimation(path) : void
    + animateMarker(currentTime) : void
    + calculatePosition(index, fraction) : [number, number]
  }
  
  class UIController {
    + showLoading(show) : void
    + displayRouteInfo(data) : void
    + clearMap() : void
    + calculateDuration(minutes) : string
  }
  
}

RouteFinderApp --> VoiceController : uses
RouteFinderApp --> CityDatabase : queries
RouteFinderApp --> AnimationController : controls
RouteFinderApp --> UIController : updates

RouteFinderApp ..> RouteServer : HTTP request

' ==========================================
' DATA TRANSFER OBJECTS
' ==========================================

package "Data Transfer" {
  
  class HTTPRequest <<DTO>> {
    + method : string = "GET"
    + url : string = "/route"
    + params : QueryParams
  }
  
  class QueryParams <<DTO>> {
    + source : string
    + destination : string
  }
  
  class HTTPResponse <<DTO>> {
    + status : string
    + distance : double
    + duration : double
    + pathNodes : int
    + pathPoints : int
    + path : Array<[double, double]>
  }
  
}

HTTPRequest --> QueryParams
RouteServer ..> HTTPRequest : receives
RouteServer ..> HTTPResponse : sends
RouteFinderApp ..> HTTPRequest : sends
RouteFinderApp ..> HTTPResponse : receives

' ==========================================
' NOTES
' ==========================================

note right of Graph
  **Data Structure:**
  - Adjacency List representation
  - HashMap for O(1) lookup
  - ArrayList for node storage
  
  **Locations:**
  - 15 major Indian cities
  - 38 Tamil Nadu districts
  Total: 53 nodes
end note

note right of DijkstraAlgorithm
  **Algorithm Complexity:**
  - Time: O((V + E) log V)
  - Space: O(V)
  
  **Features:**
  - Priority Queue optimization
  - Haversine distance
  - Path interpolation
  - Bidirectional edges
end note

note bottom of Node
  **Haversine Formula:**
  Calculates great-circle distance
  between two GPS coordinates
  on Earth's surface
  
  Returns distance in kilometers
end note

note left of RouteFinderApp
  **Browser APIs Used:**
  - Leaflet.js (mapping)
  - Web Speech API (voice I/O)
  - Fetch API (HTTP requests)
  - requestAnimationFrame (animation)
end note

note top of VoiceController
  **Voice Features:**
  - Speech Recognition (STT)
  - Speech Synthesis (TTS)
  - Language: en-IN
  - Auto-fill input fields
  - Route narration
end note

@enduml
